<p>Then you have a different problem about displaying the robot position on the field. The others in this thread have answered for the most part about the fact you need to publish your pose.</p>
<p>I can’t tell from your OP if you are using AdvantageKit or just AdvantageScope or both. They are very different things if using one and not both.</p>
<p>If you aren’t using AdvantageKit you can do something similar to this which is a Telemetry class that <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> built into their new Swerve codebase. I’ve modified it to display the swerve modules via a StructArrayPublisher that AdvantageScope is expecting the SwerveModuleState to be in.</p>
